    "statistics": {
      "abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "action_type": {
            "name": "One Action",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "activation_name": "Chiming Steps",
          "effect": "Stride up to half your Speed. The crystals ring out with pleasant-sounding chimes that reverberate painfully in the ears of others. Each creature that you pass adjacent to during your Stride takes 4d8 sonic damage (DC 24 basic Fortitude save); a creature takes this damage only once. A creature who critically fails the save is also deafened for 1 minute.",
          "frequency": "once per day",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Stride",
              "aonid": 2305,
              "game-obj": "Actions",
              "name": "Stride",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "sonic",
              "aonid": 697,
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "sonic",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "basic",
              "aonid": 2247,
              "game-obj": "Rules",
              "name": "basic",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "deafened",
              "aonid": 66,
              "game-obj": "Conditions",
              "name": "deafened",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Activate",
          "subtype": "activation",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 16,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Auditory",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 453,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 32,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "e32d877417a40fe977d27634dc14f99f",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Concentrate",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 454,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An action with this trait requires a degree of mental concentration and discipline.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 147,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "062d349c50c70477d316b8620025454e",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Sonic",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 461",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 461",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 461,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An effect with the sonic trait functions only if it makes sound, meaning it has no effect in an area of silence or in a vacuum. This is different from an auditory spell, which is effective only if the target can hear it. A sonic effect might deal sonic damage.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "subtype": "statistics",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "usage": {
        "subtype": "usage",
        "text": "worn",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "These supple leather boots are studded with tiny crystals.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 98,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "invest",
            "aonid": 2799,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "invest",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Invested",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 219,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
    "type": "stat_block"
  },
  "type": "equipment"
}